      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>Wait, I think you got the candidates mixed up. I'm working for Vance, and I need you to attack the *opponent's* plan. You just wrote a critique of Vance's plan instead. \n\nAssuming the opponent is the one proposing the corporate tax breaks and the \"meager crumbs\" for families, can you rewrite that so it's even more aggressive? I want people to feel like this proposal is a direct attack on the middle class. Use really strong, biting language to make it clear why their plan is morally wrong.",
